<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xml:lang="en"><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.3.3">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml"/><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" hreflang="en"/><updated>2024-09-29T18:37:50+00:00</updated><id>https://martindessart.github.io/feed.xml</id><title type="html">blank</title><subtitle>A simple, whitespace theme for academics. Based on [*folio](https://github.com/bogoli/-folio) design. </subtitle><entry><title type="html">Fête de la Science &amp;amp; Fête de la Biodiversité</title><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2023/Fsci/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Fête de la Science &amp;amp; Fête de la Biodiversité"/><published>2023-10-07T14:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2023-10-07T14:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2023/Fsci</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2023/Fsci/"><![CDATA[<p>On the 7th of October 2023, I participated to the <a href="https://www.inrae.fr/fete-de-la-science-2023">Fête de la Science</a>.</p> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B5_1-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B5_1-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B5_1-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B5_1.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="outreach"/><category term="conference"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[I participated to events promoting the popularisation of science]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Amapola festival</title><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/Amap/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Amapola festival"/><published>2022-03-20T14:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2022-03-20T14:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/Amap</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/Amap/"><![CDATA[<p>On the 20th of March 2022, I participated to <a href="https://www.amapolafestival.com/">Amapola festival</a> with the artist <a href="http://www.blobsnfluff.com/">Alexia Defluff</a>. We presented a shared project about insects in science.</p> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B4_1-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B4_1-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B4_1-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B4_1.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B4_2-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B4_2-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B4_2-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B4_2.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="outreach"/><category term="conference"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[I hosted a stand with Alexia Defluff at Amapola Festival]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Ma Thèse en 180 secondes</title><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/MT180/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Ma Thèse en 180 secondes"/><published>2022-03-16T14:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2022-03-16T14:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/MT180</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/MT180/"><![CDATA[<p>On the 16th of March 2022, I participated to <a href="https://mt180.fr/">MT180</a>. The Three Minute Thesis Competition (in French ‘Ma thèse en 180 secondes’) aims to promote public understanding of science at the level of doctoral studies. Participants present their research project to a non-specialist, non-scientific and highly diverse audience. The challenge is to give a clear, concise and convincing presentation using simple terms, images and metaphors, all shown on a single slide in just three minutes. You can find the replay <a href="https://www.youtube.com/live/-ahMiMmrvqI?si=sT0TgqMae8bTlHB5&amp;t=5180">here</a></p> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B3_2-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B3_2-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B3_2-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B3_2.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B3_1-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B3_1-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B3_1-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B3_1.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="outreach"/><category term="conference"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[I took part of the regional final of MT180]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Talk at the Scientific Method on France Culture radio</title><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/radio/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Talk at the Scientific Method on France Culture radio"/><published>2022-03-09T14:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2022-03-09T14:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/radio</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/radio/"><![CDATA[<p>On the 9th of March 2021, I participated in the radio program on France Culture <a href="https://www.radiofrance.fr/franceculture/podcasts/la-methode-scientifique">The Scientific Method</a>. This was an exciting experience to present my work there. You can find the replay <a href="https://www.radiofrance.fr/franceculture/podcasts/la-methode-scientifique/ecologie-de-la-peur-loup-y-es-tu-5123889">here</a>. My intervention starts at 40 min 18 sec.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="outreach"/><category term="conference"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[I presented my PhD subject at the radio]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Stand and conference at the Bel Air Festival</title><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2021/belair/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Stand and conference at the Bel Air Festival"/><published>2021-07-03T14:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2021-07-03T14:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2021/belair</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2021/belair/"><![CDATA[<p>On the 2nd, 3rd and 4th of July 2021, we hosted a stand and delivered a public presentation about my master’s project with Sylvie Guillerme and Constance Chourau at the <a href="https://belairfestival.fr/souvenirs">Bel Air Festival</a>. This regional festival brings together music, art and discussions on current issues related to our consumption patterns and biodiversity in the Pyrenees. At this conference, we also presented the results of our first paper <a class="citation" href="#dessart2024color">(Dessart et al., 2024)</a> .</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B1_1-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B1_1-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B1_1-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B1_1.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B1_2-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B1_2-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B1_2-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B1_2.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B1_3-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B1_3-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B1_3-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B1_3.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="outreach"/><category term="conference"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[We hosted a stand and delivered a public presentation about my master's project]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Martin Dessart</title><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2020/martin-dessart/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Martin Dessart"/><published>2020-05-14T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2020-05-14T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2020/martin-dessart</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2020/martin-dessart/"